1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,040
- Whenever your parents aren’t home,
you can always come eat here.

2
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:03,920
- No trouble at all.
- Thank you, ma’am.

3
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:06,720
- Want to keep studying in my room?

4
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:16,520
- Maybe number two isn’t here,
so number one feels lonely.

5
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:20,040
- Then I’ll be your close friend, Augar.
So you won’t feel lonely.

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,680
[I DON’T KNOW WHO YOU ARE,
BUT I’D LIKE TO MEET YOU.]

7
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:25,800
- Use this to tell me
if you wanna go to school together.

8
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:30,920
- Good night, Ko Neung.

9
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,480
(I finally found my answer.)

10
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:39,600
(This is my favorite time of year.)

11
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:43,600
(The season people call
the late rainy season, early winter.)

12
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,160
(I don’t exactly know why.)

13
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:50,680
(Maybe it’s because I like sitting by
the window, watching the morning dew.)

14
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:55,160
(Maybe it’s because a short school break
is near, when I get to sleep in.)

15
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,040
(Maybe because Dad becomes lively
again after taking time off from the sea.)

16
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:12,440
(Maybe it’s me wondering how sweet
winter oranges from this tree will taste.)

17
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:18,320
(Or maybe the unpredictable rain
is making my thoughts all fuzzy.)

18
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,960
Orange, wake up!

19
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:00,440
Let’s grab breakfast
at the market before school.

20
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:02,880
Why?

21
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:06,240
I’m sick of the food at home.

22
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,360
I told the gang yesterday I’d meet them.

23
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,040
And you’re only telling me now?

24
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:15,080
Well, you have to wait for me anyway.

25
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,880
Then go take a shower already.

26
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,240
We can’t be late today.

27
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,960
The teacher’s holding
a special class for the midterms.

28
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,200
I know.

29
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,680
You nag just like my mom.

30
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,920
Hey!!

31
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,280
[SRIRACHA MUNICIPAL FRESH MARKET]

32
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:54,040
Here comes your hot congee.

33
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:56,920
- Wow!
- Whoa.

34
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,240
Uncle, why don’t you
give us free fried dough sticks?

35
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:02,120
I’m the one who brought
all my friends to your diner.

36
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,160
What are you talking about?

37
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:07,000
I always give you free fried dough sticks
whenever you come here.

38
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,400
Come on.

39
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:11,320
I think I’m the reason
your diner’s still in business.

40
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,800
If I didn’t hand out your leaflets,

41
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,480
this place would’ve gone under already.

42
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:19,080
Such a foul mouth on you.

43
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,320
Fine.

44
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:24,920
Here it is.

45
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,920
Here. Share it with your friends.

46
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:27,960
Just one bag?

47
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,360
There are five of us here.

48
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,400
Gosh, look at you boys.

49
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,680
Here, take them all. I’m generous.

50
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,480
They’re all yours.

51
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,720
Here.

52
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,440
Thank you, uncle.

53
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,480
See?

54
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:48,880
- I’m famous.
- “I’m famous.”

55
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:49,560
I know.

56
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,640
You don’t have to announce it.

57
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,160
You’re quick-witted.

58
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,600
He, midterms are coming up.

59
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,960
We should help each other study.

60
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,720
Come on, Achi.

61
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,960
Anything school-related
should be discussed in class.

62
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,560
This is your punishment for saying that.

63
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:09,880
I told you already.

64
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,360
In this gang, food comes first.

65
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,400
Studying comes eventually.

66
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,480
Augar, give that back.

67
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,720
You’re too late.

68
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,040
But Achi’s right.

69
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:26,080
Grade 10 is the foundation of high school.

70
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,440
If we don’t work hard now,
it could affect us later on.

71
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,640
Way to kill the mood.

72
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,840
Even congee and dough sticks
can’t save this now.

73
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:47,000
Do you think there’s a pill we could take
and wake up as adults?

74
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:50,200
Just freeze yourself like Captain America.

75
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,360
Yeah, sounds interesting.

76
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,480
I’m being sarcastic.

77
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:55,640
Oh?

78
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:57,720
Hey, boys.

79
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,960
Why aren’t you at school yet?

80
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:02,080
Should I call Mr. Kong?

81
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:02,800
Huh?
Hello, sir.

82
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:04,800
Hello, sir.

83
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,240
Why would you call Mr. Kong, Dad?

84
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:09,000
It’s not time for school yet.

85
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:09,680
Yeah?
Mm.

86
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:16,360
Midterms are coming up,

87
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:18,400
so we came here to
study together before class.

88
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:21,040
- Hey! Seriously?
- Of course.

89
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,800
This group is so impressive.

90
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,840
It was Boss Ko’s idea
for us to study together.

91
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,760
What nonsense.

92
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:28,800
Uncle!

93
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,680
I’m not buying that for a second, Boss Ko.

94
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,520
Oh, hey. The rain finally stopped.

95
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,600
Anyone want to go out to sea with me?

96
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:42,480
After exams, I’ll take care of everything.

97
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:43,480
- Me!
- Me!

98
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,160
The three of us, sir.

99
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,240
This is a democracy, so we all have to go.

100
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,720
Yes, attaboy!

101
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,200
That’s amazing, sons.

102
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,040
Attaboy!

103
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:11,720
I hope you all do well on
your first midterms as high school students.

104
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,080
Make sure to study hard for them.
[MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 25, 2000]

105
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,960
Make sure to study hard for them.
[MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 25, 2000]

106
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,320
Yes, sir.

107
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:21,000
Sir, can I go study in the library?

108
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,080
Of course.

109
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:24,720
I already gave you all the exam guidelines.

110
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:29,240
The rest is up to you now.

111
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:33,520
And during other teachers’ periods,
you still have to attend class as usual.

112
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,360
Yes, sir.

113
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,160
Class.

114
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,600
- Thank you, sir.
- Thank you, sir.

115
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,440
You’re very hardworking.

116
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,400
Maybe you’re just too lazy.

117
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,680
(Asshole.)

118
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,920
Tle, can I ask you something?

119
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:54,840
Mm-hm.

120
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:58,320
Did you leave a note on my desk?

121
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:02,240
Or did you see anyone hanging around it?

122
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,920
I mind my own business, August.

123
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,800
I don’t really pay attention to other people.

124
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,560
Bye now.

125
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:26,800
What’s wrong?

126
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,920
Do you think
this is the last rain of the season?

127
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:45,080
How would I know?

128
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:48,920
You’re smart about everything.

129
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:49,800
I thought you’d know.

130
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,680
You’re good at stuff like this.

131
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,160
You should spend more time studying.

132
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,320
I’ve got Ko Song with me.

133
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:01,840
I don’t need to study.

134
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:14,320
So what if this is the last rain of the year?

135
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,320
I can’t tell you.

136
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,360
I’m scared it’ll come true.

137
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:46,200
Once you’re done studying, don’t forget to
do some exercises to test yourself.

138
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,800
I know.

139
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:54,920
When Boss Ko gets serious
about something, nobody can beat him.

140
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,160
We’ll see.

141
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,440
Thanks a lot.

142
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:28,920
Hm?

143
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,560
For helping you study?

144
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,200
For leaving me that notebook the other day.

145
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,360
No problem.

146
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:39,120
I have a senior in Sports Science.

147
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,600
I got all that info from them.

148
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,400
Thanks again.

149
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:45,040
Mm.

150
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:48,120
So, how’s your ankle?

151
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,280
I followed all your advice.

152
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,120
I’m fully recovered now.

153
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,600
Very good.

154
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,960
See? Good things happen
when you listen to me.

155
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,160
I think you should start
listening to me about studying too.

156
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,840
Please. I don’t think so.

157
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:03,080
Hey, but you must.

158
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:06,200
I’m planning to get into university
through the athlete quota.

159
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:08,120
Ah. How about this?

160
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,960
You focus on the important parts only.

161
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,200
This one too.

162
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:30,160
MIDTERM EXAMS

163
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:39,320
Let’s test your memory before I teach you
a trick for memorizing the periodic table.

164
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,600
What’s 97?

165
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:41,400
Cs.
Counter-Strike.

166
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:43,360
It’s Caesium.

167
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,720
Can you be serious for once, Augar?

168
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,000
Yeah, try being serious.

169
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,520
You’re the one reading a comic book.

170
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,520
Wake up, Ko Neung.

171
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,560
Next, what’s Ca?

172
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:56,320
Canada!

173
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,360
Just go back to sleep, Ko Neung.

174
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,080
How many time-outs are allowed
per set in volleyball?

175
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:05,600
One!

176
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,160
- Two?
- Two?

177
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,560
Gosh, I don’t want to study anymore.

178
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:09,720
Next question.

179
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,040
Listen carefully.

180
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:19,080
Mark was nervous about
asking Jane to the school dance,

181
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:23,880
so his friend told him to [...] and just do it.

182
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,320
A. back up

183
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,480
B. look out

184
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,840
C. go for it

185
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,880
Which one’s correct?

186
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,640
This is a book.

187
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,920
- Cheers to the school break!
- Cheers to the school break!

188
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,280
Yeah!

189
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,320
I’m gonna sleep all I want.

190
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,240
I’m gonna watch movies
until my eyes give out.

191
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,960
And we’ll have tons of time to study.

192
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:11,880
Jeez!

193
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,000
What about you, August?

194
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,480
You guys look way too happy.

195
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,480
I’ve got two retests to take. Damn it!

196
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:22,000
That’s because you’re
addicted to comic books.

197
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,040
Because I love reading.

198
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,400
Yeah, comic books only.

199
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,040
Hey, cut it out.

200
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,680
Where’s Ko Song anyway?

201
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:33,400
I left the room right after him.

202
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:36,800
I saw him talking to Mr. Kong,
then he ran off somewhere.

203
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,240
Where’d he go?

204
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,440
It’s been three days already.

205
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,440
Where did Ko Song go?

206
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:55,840
Exactly.

207
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:58,400
Don’t tell me he moved away.

208
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:04,680
Ko Song doesn’t usually
tell us what he’s up to.

209
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,480
Right.

210
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,440
- August.
- Hm?

211
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,280
Didn’t you see Mr. Kong during your retests?

212
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,040
No.

213
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,120
Mr. Prateep supervised mine.

214
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:17,480
Damn.

215
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:18,400
I’ve got chills.

216
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,280
Boss Ko.

217
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:38,040
Didn’t Ko Song tell you anything?

218
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,720
No.

219
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:43,640
I think he’ll be back soon.

220
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:46,760
Maybe he has some
family matters to deal with.

221
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,000
Like…

222
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,360
Moving away?

223
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,720
Stop saying that, you jerk.

224
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,320
Open your eyes and look.

225
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:02,640
No cars.

226
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,560
The house is locked.

227
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:06,440
Even the shoes are gone.

228
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:56,400
Ko.

229
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:02,960
Remember when you asked
what the last rain meant?

230
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:11,680
This was the meaning
I was too afraid to say out loud.

231
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,440
I’ll be right back.

232
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,200
You can keep playing.

233
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,440
I just came here with my mom
to get some exercise.

234
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,480
Where’s your mom?

235
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:37,320
Probably walking around
with the aunties somewhere.

236
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:46,120
So… have you been here long?

237
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:50,520
Long enough to see that
your ankle’s doing just fine.

238
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:55,560
Wow, you’re like
a personal trainer for athletes.

239
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:56,360
Hey.

240
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:59,080
Do you think I should
study Sports Science like my senior?

241
00:17:59,120 --> 00:17:59,880
Good idea.

242
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,440
I want to become
a professional basketball player too.

243
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:02,840
That way, we can always stay together.

244
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:04,920
That what you want?

245
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,360
Would you like that?

246
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:12,080
I think...

247
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,360
I would.

248
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:20,160
Okay. Deal?

249
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,160
Mm. Deal.

250
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:30,160
I’m going back to the game.

251
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:31,120
Mm.

252
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:56,160
[I DON’T KNOW WHO YOU ARE,
BUT I’D LIKE TO MEET YOU.]

253
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:07,000
[I WENT TO THE BEACH ON SAT,
BUT I DIDN’T SEE YOU.]

254
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:30,200
[COME SEE ME AFTER THE EXAMS.]

255
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:55,480
Here you go, boys. Food’s here.

256
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:56,800
Dig in.

257
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:59,040
- Whoa! Thank you, ma’am.
- Whoa! Thank you, ma’am.

258
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:00,120
Of course.

259
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,160
If I finish all this, I’ll stay full for two weeks.

260
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:04,320
Want me to pack some
for your mom too, August, Augar?

261
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:04,840
Yes, ma’am.

262
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:06,400
Okay. How about you, Achi?

263
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,160
I’ll make you a fresh set.

264
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:09,520
Yes, ma’am. Thank you so much.

265
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:10,320
No problem, dear.

266
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,520
So, are you going out to sea with us?

267
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:14,160
My husband invited me too,

268
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:17,080
but you boys should go.

269
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:22,040
I’ve got a “Math class” with the moms.

270
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:24,480
Ah, I see.

271
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:26,600
Go on, eat up.

272
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:29,360
So, are you boys ready for the trip?

273
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,120
- We are.
- We are.

274
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:31,920
Great.

275
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:33,840
I brought this too, sir.

276
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:35,800
What’s that?

277
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:38,400
A parental consent form.

278
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:38,960
What?

279
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:40,960
Honey!

280
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,080
Wait a second.

281
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,320
Do we really have to do this, son?

282
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,560
Who told you to make that, dear?

283
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:48,520
Don’t people normally do this?

284
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,880
Still, it’s good, Achi.

285
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,120
At least your mom will know
where you’re going.

286
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:53,880
After the fishing trip,

287
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,440
you’ll have to grade Achi too, sir.

288
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:56,480
Do I have to?

289
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:57,920
Fine then.
You keep it yourself.

290
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:02,000
Honey, sit and eat with the boys.

291
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,680
I’ll go get more food.

292
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:04,680
Honey.
What?

293
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,120
Are you really not coming with us?

294
00:21:07,280 --> 00:21:07,680
It’s hot.

295
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,920
You hardly go out in the sun these days.

296
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:12,920
Gosh. It’s hot.

297
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:14,640
Come on, boys. Eat up.

298
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:16,600
Eat as much as you want.

299
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:20,960
Eat.

300
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:28,600
Didn’t we promise Ko Song
we’d all go together?

301
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,200
Shouldn’t we wait for him?

302
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:49,960
True. We still have one more week
before school starts.

303
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,720
Yeah, I think so too.

304
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,320
I need to practice basketball anyway.

305
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,840
I’m making the school team
in 11th grade for sure.

306
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:56,920
No problem.

307
00:21:57,280 --> 00:21:59,480
I’ll have my mom sign the form again later.

308
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:01,840
The sea’s not running out of fish
anytime soon, right, sir?

309
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:03,200
Mm.

310
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:07,880
Hey, relax.

311
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:09,280
I was just saying.

312
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:12,400
If Ko Song can’t come, that’s okay too.

313
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,320
I’m not that serious.

314
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:16,680
I’m good with anything.

315
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:22,160
But I think we should wait
so we can all go together.

316
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:24,240
I’ll take the big boat out.

317
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,440
Come on, boys. Go ahead and eat.

318
00:22:27,760 --> 00:22:30,200
An army marches on its stomach.

319
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:31,800
Eat up.

320
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,160
Have this fish.

321
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:35,960
I didn’t catch it. Ko’s mom bought it.

322
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,840
Here. She made the Som Tum too.

323
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,800
You boys can have it. I’m not touching it.

324
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,400
I’m kidding.

325
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,320
Come on, Ko. Dig in.

326
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,160
Eat as much as you want.

327
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,960
If an orange falls…

328
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,640
it means you’re coming back.

329
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:03,920
Orange!

330
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,960
Why didn’t you tell us
where you were going?

331
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:44,760
I’m sorry.

332
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,560
- Ah!
- Ah!

333
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,640
I already smacked him to teach him a lesson.

334
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:59,880
Next time you disappear without
telling us anything, you’re out of the gang.

335
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,800
Wow, Boss Ko’s so scary.

336
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,920
When he was gone,
you were acting like a sad little puppy.

337
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:05,200
Like hell I was.

338
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:06,840
I was in a rush.

339
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,320
The moment I walked out of the exam room,

340
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:11,640
Mr. Kong told me my mom had called
and wanted me home immediately.

341
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,440
How’s your grandmother?

342
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,680
She still hasn’t recovered yet.

343
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:18,520
Dad and I came back first.

344
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:19,800
My mom stayed there to take care of her.

345
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,720
Part of getting old, I guess.

346
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,640
How old is your grandma now?

347
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:25,760
82.

348
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:27,760
Damn. Quite an age.

349
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,040
She’s been healthy her whole life,

350
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:33,240
but age is catching up to her now.

351
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:39,480
(Students taking the final day of retests,
please gather in the auditorium.)

352
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:40,200
That’s my cue.

353
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:41,120
I’m off now.

354
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:42,400
Good luck, dude.

355
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,440
I hope you fail and have to retake it.

356
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:45,880
Watch your mouth.

357
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:47,520
I’ll hire someone to break your leg.

358
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:48,480
I’m not scared.

359
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:49,920
I’ve got Achi’s medical team backing me up.

360
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,520
- Bring it on.
- Bring it on.

361
00:25:51,920 --> 00:25:52,960
Go do your retest.

362
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,640
Your grandma’s always been strong.

363
00:25:58,960 --> 00:25:59,840
I’m sure she’ll be okay.

364
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:03,960
I hope so.

365
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:08,600
So, how was the fishing trip?

366
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:10,280
We haven’t gone yet

367
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:12,000
because Ko Neung said—
We were worried about the storm!

368
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,960
We were worried about the storm,

369
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:19,480
so we postponed it.

370
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:21,120
Ah!

371
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:24,920
We will finally head out to sea
after August finishes his retests.

372
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,600
- Let’s go!
- Yeah!

373
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:29,040
Anyone want ice cream? My treat.

374
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:30,080
I do.

375
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,200
Let’s go.

376
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,640
Let’s go!

377
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:41,600
Tomorrow, let’s see
who catches the most fish.

378
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:46,040
Boss Ko, why don’t you
tell them who won last time?

379
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:48,000
Yeah, yeah, you were insanely good.

380
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,840
All you did was fish.

381
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,440
August and I took naps sometimes.

382
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:53,720
Augar stayed up the whole night.

383
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:55,120
Who could beat you?

384
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,480
No, you just sucked.

385
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:57,760
Everyone else caught fish,

386
00:26:57,960 --> 00:27:00,280
but you caught an octopus
and got ink sprayed all over your face.

387
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,440
Your whole face went black.

388
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:02,400
It was hilarious.

389
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:04,320
August laughed so hard
he almost fell off the boat.

390
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:06,920
That sounds nonsensical.

391
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:07,720
Who’s gonna believe you?

392
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,600
Knowing Ko Neung,
I can believe that happened.

393
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:10,240
Hey.

394
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:18,280
Hey, August.

395
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,480
What’s wrong?

396
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:24,880
Did you fail the retest?

397
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,120
Seriously?

398
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:27,320
August.

399
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:29,200
August, calm down.

400
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,120
They’re not replying.

401
00:27:33,480 --> 00:27:33,960
What?

402
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,760
That person’s not replying to my notes.

403
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:40,280
Damn you. I thought
you were upset about the exam.

404
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,280
Did you guys prank me?

405
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:43,520
Just admit it already.

406
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:46,600
You know we always confess
whenever we prank you.

407
00:27:48,320 --> 00:27:50,240
Fine, I’ll tell the truth.

408
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:52,160
It was me, okay?

409
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:53,040
Can we move on now?
Really?

410
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,120
Yeah. It’s me.

411
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,680
That’s not true, Argar. You’re totally lying.

412
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:03,280
Someone really did leave me a note.

413
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:06,200
There, there, little August.

414
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:07,080
Don’t be sad.

415
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:10,000
Maybe they gave it to the wrong person.

416
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:11,280
Holy shit.

417
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:13,200
You might be right.

418
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:16,200
The note never said who it was for.

419
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,480
August, don’t be sad.

420
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:21,360
How about some ice cream?
I’m buying.

421
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:23,920
Ice cream?
Mm.

422
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:24,560
Let’s go.

423
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:25,800
Can I get three?

424
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:26,360
Of course.

425
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:27,440
Come on.

426
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,600
Damn, this dude got over it fast.

427
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,200
He really loves free stuff.

428
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,840
Three cups of ice cream, please.

429
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:33,440
What’s wrong?

430
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,200
Grandma still hasn’t recovered yet.

431
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:42,640
Mom said she’ll
have to stay there for a while.

432
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:47,520
Dad’s going to travel back and forth
between here and Mom’s place.

433
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:55,320
Did your dad just leave?

434
00:29:58,280 --> 00:29:59,200
He did.

435
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:03,160
What are you doing?

436
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:06,560
Nothing.

437
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,160
Want to go out?

438
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:35,040
It feels nice getting some fresh air.

439
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,480
We shouldn’t stay cooped up
at home during break.

440
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:40,520
Mm.

441
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:42,000
It’s nice.

442
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:54,480
Come to think of it,
the ocean’s pretty scary.

443
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:57,200
It’s very scary.

444
00:30:58,200 --> 00:30:59,480
Especially when you can’t see it.

445
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:07,800
That...

446
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:09,440
What’s that light?

447
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:12,000
That’s us.

448
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:14,160
We’re about to head out to sea.

449
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:19,160
Once we’re out there,
we forget how scary the ocean is.

450
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:24,600
But you didn’t seem that excited
when your dad asked, Orange.

451
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,680
It’s not that I hate going out to sea.

452
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,200
I’m just lazy.

453
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:32,200
Then why did you agree to go this time?

454
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,280
Because…

455
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:41,240
it’s your first time going out to sea.

456
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,880
And Achi’s too.

457
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:05,480
Besides, if Boss Ko doesn’t come,

458
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:06,800
where’s the fun in that?

459
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:20,280
Thanks for taking me out
to get some fresh air.

460
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:24,960
Mm.

461
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,120
You’ve got everything?

462
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:57,720
Yep.

463
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:59,080
Nope. One thing’s missing.

464
00:32:59,120 --> 00:32:59,600
What is it?
You, honey.

465
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:07,840
Wow, you boys look more than ready.

466
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:09,320
Of course, sir.

467
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:10,200
I’m the defending champion.

468
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:11,440
Gotta show these amateurs how it’s done.

469
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:12,920
He’s been bragging the whole way here.

470
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:14,600
So annoying.

471
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,600
Sir, August just got his heart broken.

472
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:18,280
We should throw him a party.

473
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:19,480
Let’s do it!

474
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:20,360
Yeah!

475
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:21,640
Hold on.

476
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:24,360
Once your mom gets here,
I’m telling her everything, August.

477
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:25,520
Please don’t.

478
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:26,880
Heartbreak is enough already.

479
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:29,480
Save his butt from getting spanked.

480
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:36,400
Whoa.

481
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:40,880
Yeah.

482
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:42,880
That’s so cool.

483
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:45,320
That’s the kind of life I want.

484
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:46,600
What’s going on?

485
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:50,400
Stunned by my charm and good looks?

486
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:52,000
What is it, everyone?

487
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:57,280
Hey, where’s the other Ko?

488
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,240
I’m here.

489
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:00,080
There he is.

490
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,920
We’ve got the oranges, so we’re ready to go!

491
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,440
You’re free to go.

492
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:06,120
Go on.

493
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:07,160
Hold on, guys.

494
00:34:09,640 --> 00:34:10,440
The consent form, sir.

495
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:12,000
- Jeez!
- Jeez!

496
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:15,720
Come on, boys!

497
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,320
Slow down. No need to run.

498
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:23,400
Come on, Ko Song.

499
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:25,320
Hello, sir.

500
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:27,280
August, come on.

501
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:28,960
Go easy.

502
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:34,720
Ready, tigers?

503
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:35,720
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

504
00:34:35,720 --> 00:34:37,040
Let’s go.

505
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:49,440
I’m gonna be King of the Pirates!

506
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,080
So? How is it?

507
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:01,800
Told you it’d be cool.

508
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:55,720
Ko, Ko, Ko.
Look.

509
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:12,360
I’ve got four already, little August.

510
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:13,760
How about you?

511
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:15,480
Quit distracting me.

512
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,800
I’m only one behind.

513
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:19,040
What about you, Achi?

514
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:19,880
Huh?

515
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:21,600
How many fish have you caught?

516
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:24,960
Uh... I think around seven or eight.

517
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:29,920
Hey, that’s okay.

518
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,560
It’s your first time.

519
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:32,760
It’s normal not to catch many fish.

520
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:33,200
Mm.

521
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:36,080
(Damn.)

522
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:49,760
How are you, son?

523
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,200
Feeling better after the medicine?

524
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:52,320
Yes, sir.

525
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:54,760
It might make you a little sleepy, though.

526
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:58,160
If you need anything, just tell me or Ko.

527
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:05,320
Are you okay?

528
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:09,640
What a shame.

529
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,480
Getting seasick on my first time out at sea.

530
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:15,400
It’s nothing to be ashamed of.

531
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,120
It’s not an illness.

532
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:19,160
You’ll get used to it
if you come out here often.

533
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:21,600
If you don’t quit first, I mean.

534
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,960
This is my first and last trip.

535
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,360
Hey, don’t speak too soon.

536
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,840
Let’s try it. I’ve got you.

537
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:53,920
Don’t worry.

538
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,040
I’m not letting go of your hand.

539
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,080
Easy now.

540
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:11,160
Whoa.

541
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,200
Do you believe me now
when I say it’s beautiful?

542
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:23,560
Want to go over to the others?

543
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:25,960
But I’m not carrying you.

544
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:28,280
I’m only holding your hand like this.

545
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:31,240
Let’s go.

546
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,520
Come on. Watch your step.

547
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:41,320
How are you feeling, Ko Song?

548
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,000
Better now.

549
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:44,760
Want to try fishing?

550
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:46,520
Don’t be scared of falling off the boat.

551
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:47,360
We can all swim.

552
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:49,480
Have fun, Augar, August.

553
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:51,360
I’m starting to get sleepy.

554
00:38:52,600 --> 00:38:54,240
Fishing’s actually pretty fun.

555
00:38:54,640 --> 00:38:56,160
I’ve completely lost track of time.

556
00:38:56,800 --> 00:38:57,320
Yeah.

557
00:38:57,840 --> 00:39:00,720
I’m getting sleepy too.

558
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:03,400
Guys, the sun’s going to rise from that side.

559
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:05,400
Let’s wake up early and watch it together.

560
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:06,360
Sure.

561
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:08,480
Of course. I’m usually up early anyway.

562
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:10,520
I can stay awake all night until sunrise.

563
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:11,920
Wow.

564
00:39:12,120 --> 00:39:13,920
Unless the medicine knocks me out.

565
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:43,440
Orange.
Hm?

566
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,000
Thanks for being my friend.

567
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:55,600
I won’t disappear again.

568
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:06,440
(The last rain of the season
doesn’t just mark a change in weather.)

569
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:15,080
(It’s also the moment
unpredictability begins to fade into clarity.)

570
00:40:21,760 --> 00:40:24,400
(A phrase suddenly comes to my mind.)

571
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:31,760
(“The sky is always beautiful after the rain.”)

572
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:41,800
(And for the first time,
I think it truly is beautiful.)

573
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:51,480
(But whether it’s a good thing or not...)

574
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:56,120
(I don’t really know.)

575
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,800
- Yay!
- Yay!

576
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,040
- Yeah!

577
00:41:44,080 --> 00:41:46,560
- So, what do you like, Orange?

578
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,000
- You like Ko Song, don’t you?

579
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:50,720
- Uh...

580
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:53,000
- I think I already like someone.

581
00:41:53,080 --> 00:41:54,880
- I already like someone, too.

582
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:01,400
- Why not plant an orange tree at your house
since you like oranges so much?

583
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:04,440
- I only like the one next door. That’s it.

584
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:08,600
- What about you?
Do you like having me around?
